Race.FullText: Shall the Parish of Winn, State of Louisiana (the ''Parish"), levy a special tax of five (5) mills on all property subject to taxation in the Parish (an estimated $323,000 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of five (5) years, beginning with the year 2015 and ending with the year 2019, for the purpose of maintaining and supporting, for acquiring sites, or erecting, or renovating buildings, or performing capital improvements on existing buildings thereon or additions thereto, including furniture, fixtures and equipment for the Winn Parish Library, title to which shall be in the public, and further authority in the event that said election is carried, to levy and collect said tax?

Shall Road District #1 of the Parish of Winn, State of Louisiana (the "District"), levy a special tax of two and two hundredths (2.02) mills on all property subject to taxation in the District (which is within the corporate limits of the City of Winnfield, Parish of Winn, State of Louisiana) (an estimated $37,000 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of five (5) years, beginning with the year 2015 and ending with the year 2019, for the purpose of constructing, repairing and maintaining streets and bridges, title to which shall be in the public, and further authority in the event that said election is carried, to levy and collect said tax?

Shall Road District #2 of the Parish of Winn, State of Louisiana (the "District"), levy a special tax of five (5) mills on all property subject to taxation in the District (which is outside the corporate limits of the City of Winnfield, Parish of Winn, State of Louisiana) (an estimated $230,000 reasonably expected at this time to be collected from the levy of the tax for an entire year), for a period of five (5) years, beginning with the year 2015 and ending with the year 2019, for the purpose of constructing, repairing and maintaining public roads and bridges, title to which shall be in the public, and further authority in the event that said election is carried, to levy and collect said tax?
